From 26cbc493a4d6b6d78b184bc1dd840d4906aa6232 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: boris-unckel <bu.githubcom@mail.unckel.net>
Date: Thu, 9 Apr 2026 07:47:29 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] SEC-AUDIT-003: add CSP header to
 replacementImageResponse()
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Previously the placeholder SVG response (used for NOT FOUND, XSS
block, INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR and all other error fallback paths
in ImageFactory, MediaFileThumbnail, MediaFileDownload) returned
only `content-type: image/svg+xml` — no Content-Security-Policy.

The regular imageResponse() path already sets
`content-security-policy: script-src none;frame-src none` as a
defense-in-depth barrier against active content in SVG/HTML
bodies. The placeholder path did not, which is inconsistent and
removes a future safety net: if a later change ever interpolates
user-controlled text into the placeholder body (filename,
exception message, …), there is no CSP to block inline scripts.

This commit fixes the method so every caller inherits the same
strict CSP without touching any of the 13 call sites. The symmetry
with imageResponse() is now explicit and the SEC-AUDIT-003 test
from the previous commit passes.

No behaviour change for existing SVG placeholders (static text).
Defense-in-depth only; no known exploitable primitive today.
---
 app/Factories/ImageFactory.php | 6 +++++-
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/app/Factories/ImageFactory.php b/app/Factories/ImageFactory.php
index 0e39d7993b..1de9ad2179 100644
--- a/app/Factories/ImageFactory.php
+++ b/app/Factories/ImageFactory.php
@@ -260,8 +260,12 @@ class ImageFactory implements ImageFactoryInterface
         $svg = view(name: 'errors/image-svg', data: ['status' => $text]);
 
         // We can't send the actual status code, as browsers won't show images with 4xx/5xx.
+        // We set the same strict Content-Security-Policy as imageResponse() so the
+        // placeholder SVG cannot execute inline scripts even if a future change
+        // introduces user-controlled substitutions into the placeholder body.
         return response(content: $svg, code: StatusCodeInterface::STATUS_OK, headers: [
-            'content-type' => 'image/svg+xml',
+            'content-type'            => 'image/svg+xml',
+            'content-security-policy' => 'script-src none;frame-src none',
         ]);
     }
 
